FBIS3-15542 "drsov045_g_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-045 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Mar 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus 900 Military Units Undergo Reform WS0703151494 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1200 GMT 7 Mar 94 WS0703151494 Minsk BELAPAN Language: Belarusian Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "Belarusian Army Is Being Reformed"] [Text] Lieutenant General Mikalay Churkin, first deputy Belarusian defense minister, stated at a session of the Defense Ministry Collegium that in 1992-93, more than 900 units of the Belarusian Armed Forces underwent a reform in which numerical strength corresponded to the quantitative parameters foreseen by international agreements for Belarus.
